      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "# What's New\r\n\r\n## Progressive Outline Folding\r\n\r\nAdded **Fold more** and **Fold less** commands that operate on all selected visible headings at once.\r\n\r\n**How to use:**\r\n0. Configure new hotkeys in Obsidian for commands \"Heading Outliner: Fold More\" and \"Heading Outliner: Fold Less\"\r\n1. Use Obsidian's built-in **Fold all headings and lists** to collapse everything\r\n2. Select all (`Ctrl+A`) or select specific sections\r\n3. Run **Fold less** to reveal one heading level at a time\r\n4. Run **Fold more** to collapse back down\r\n\r\nWhen nothing is selected, commands fall back to the heading under the cursor.\r\n\r\nCloses #1  - thanks @freecicero for the great suggestion!",
